The paper discusses Open Domain Question Answering (QA) using a combination of Knowledge Bases (KBs) and entity-linked text, which falls under the sub-categories of Natural Language Processing (NLP) and Artificial Intelligence (AI). The paper also mentions the use of deep neural networks, which is a common technique in Machine Learning (ML) and Deep Learning (DL), falling under the sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses graph representation learning, which is a technique used in Information Retrieval (IR) and Database (DB) systems, falling under the sub-categories of cs.IR and cs.DB. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, and cs.DB.
